title: Ibrahimovic's Sweden faces Denmark in Euros playoff derby
text:
Photo: FREDRIK SANDBERG/TT, AP Image 1 of / 1   1 Sweden's Zlatan Ibrahimovic celebrates scoring the opening goal during the UEFA Euro 2016 group G qualifying soccer match between Sweden and Moldova at Friends Arena in Stockholm, Sweden, on Monday Oct. 12, 2015. (Fredrik Sandberg / TT via AP) SWEDEN OUT Sweden's Zlatan Ibrahimovic celebrates scoring the opening goal during the UEFA Euro 2016 group G qualifying soccer match between Sweden and Moldova at Friends Arena in Stockholm, Sweden, on Monday Oct. 12, ... more Photo: FREDRIK SANDBERG/TT, AP Ibrahimovic's Sweden faces Denmark in Euros playoff derby 1  /  1 Back to Gallery NYON, Switzerland (AP) â€” Zlatan Ibrahimovic 's Sweden will face Denmark in a Nordic derby in the Euro 2016 playoffs.
Norway, another Nordic nation chasing one of the remaining four spots at the expanded 24-team tournament, was drawn Sunday to play Hungary in the two-legged playoffs next month.
Ireland, which qualified for Euro 2012 through the playoffs, faces Bosnia-Herzegovina this time. In a repeat of a Euro 2000 playoff, Ukraine and Slovenia were paired together again. Slovenia won back in 1999.
Alongside host nation France, the other finalists so far are: Albania, Austria, Belgium, Croatia, the Czech Republic, England, Germany, Iceland, Italy, Northern Ireland, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Russia, Slovakia, Spain, Switzerland, Turkey and Wales.
